line_1: 'Twere nobler far to play the Christian's part,
line_2: Aid struggling Conscience to secure his heart,

line_1: And teach the diffident, discreeter part
line_2: Still scorn, with conscious pride, the mask of Art;

line_1: And Rays of Nature shone in ev'ry Part.
line_2: Both these displeas'd her, tho' judicious Art,

line_1: And I have liv'd; and We must part.
line_2: Dear Idol of My panting Heart,
